comments.body:
@TomSweeneyRedHat can correct me, but IIUC, the runc maintainers didn't wanna backport the fixes to the existing runc on this branch. And I'd be surprised if we're NOT shipping that updated buildah.

I totally hear you on the library bumps and I had raised that concern with Tom before, but I guess the alternative would be we try to backport patches ourselves to the current runc OR we just bump podman to the version that's known to work with these library versions.

I haven't run the other tests myself, but I'll give it a go. Don't know if SE has run them already.

@Luap99 I'm not sure of the exact need, but what drove the bump of common and friends was this commit, ["Update github.com/containers/image/v5 to get updated docker-daemon:"](https://github.com/containers/buildah/pull/6538/commits/4f6e12d5e2944ec8653692fcf1650d8643d4adc5) in the PR (https://github.com/containers/buildah/pull/6538) that bumped Buildah up for the runc fixes.  Nalin and Chris were trying to get stuff out under a huge pressure crunch.  I reviewed the commit, but I didn't catch the bump to common and friends.  

I fear the change might have been made just to get the conformance tests working, and we might have been better served not doing that and just changing the tests.  

@nalind or @cevich any further thoughts?  

And Yes, Buildah with those bumps has been released, do we need to reconsider and revert that patch?
